descript.abstract: The 111th Congressional District Boundaries data set contains geographic information for the political entities of the 111th Congressional districts.
descript.purpose: The data provide users with information about the locations of congressional districts, primarily for national planning applications.

idinfo.useconst: None. Acknowledgment of the Research and Innovative Technology Administration's Bureau of Transportation Statistics (RITA/BTS) National Transportation Atlas Database (NTAD) 2010 would be appreciated in products derived from these data.

attracc.attraccr: Attributes for the 111th Congressional District data set were created in a consistent manner using similar tolerances.

dataqual.logic: All node-link and polygon topological relationships were created and verified using ARC/INFO, a Geographic Information System. The unique identifiers were verified using ARC/INFO. The data was then converted to a shapefile format.
dataqual.complete: This data set is composed of the 437 Districts having voting representation plus two districts without voting rights the District of Columbia and Puerto Rico.

horizpa.horizpar: The Congressional District data set was created from TIGER/Line data having a nominal scale of 1:100,000.

srcinfo.srccontr: Spatial information for the 111th Congressional District boundaries.

procstep.procdesc: Individual files for the Congressional Districts in Alaska, Hawaii, Puerto Rico, and the 48 contiguous states were merged into a single data set using ARC/INFO. After completing topological and attribute verification using ARC/INFO, the data was converted into shapefile format.

procstep.procdesc: Downloaded the shapefile from BOC. Downloaded congressional district information from USGS (http://www-atlas.usgs.gov/mld/cgd109p.html ) and joined the spatial with the latest attribute data on distritic reprsentatives. Used ArcGIS for topological and attribute verification.

procstep.procdesc: Downloaded the shapefile from BOC. Downloaded congressional district information from USGS (http://www-atlas.usgs.gov/mld/cgd109p.html ) and joined the spatial with the latest attribute data on district representatives. Used ArcGIS for topological and attribute verification. 110th Congressional District Boundaries did not change from the 109th.
